definition.value: An organic thiophosphate that is S,S'-methanediyl bis[dihydrogen (phosphorodithioate)] in which all the hydroxy groups have been converted to their corresponding ethyl esters respectively. Ethion is an organophosphate insecticide with inhibitory activity towards the enzyme acetylcholinesterase ( EC 3.1.1.7).
Any flavonoid with a 3,4-dihydro-2-aryl-2H-1-benzopyran skeleton and its substituted derivatives.
Any chromene bearing one or more substituted or unsubstituted amino groups.
Any member of the class of  biphenyls that is a mono or poly-substituted biphenyl having fluro group as one of the substituents.
A C-nitro compound in which the nitro group is attached at C-4 of m-cresol.
Any hydroxyflavone carrying four hydroxy substituents.
An epoxide that is oxirane substituted by a methyl group at position 2.
Any hydroxyflavone in which two ring hydrogens are replaced by hydroxy substituents.
A hydroxyflavone carrying a single hydroxy substituent.
The simplest member of the class of flavans that is chromane substituted by a phenyl group at position 2.

Any  flavonoid that is a salt containing flavylium ion or 2-phenylchromenylium skeleton and its substituted derivatives together with an appropriate counterion.  Aglycons of anthocyanins, they form a part of the large group of planr pigments.
An organic chloride salt of any anthocyanidin.
Any flavonoid that is a glycoside derivative of anthocyanidin. Anthocyanins are water-souluble plant pigments that generally occur as acidic salts exhibiting bright colours.
An organic chloride salt of any anthocyanin.
An anthocyanidin chloride that has delphinidin as the cationic counterpart.
A benzoate ester that is the isopropyl ester of salicylic acid.
Substance used to treat lice (genus Pediculus) infestation.
